{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01USwp44vfoUcphBR1R3zEh1","type":"tool_result","content":"  5110→4. **Never defer \"kill the process\" actions.** \"Kill Ralph\" has been a P0 action item since session 17. It was never executed. 13+ sessions of waste followed.\n  5111→5. **Avoid accumulating retro cost on no-op sessions.** Retros should be skipped or minimal when no productive work occurred.\n  5112→\n  5113→## 7. Action Items\n  5114→\n  5115→| Priority | Action | Owner | Status |\n  5116→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n  5117→| **P0** | **Kill Ralph NOW.** `kill $(cat ralph/.pid)` or equivalent. Sprint is done. Every additional second is waste. | User | OVERDUE — first flagged session 17 |\n  5118→| **P0** | **Add sprint-complete auto-termination to Ralph.** Exit when `doneCount === totalCount`. | Next sprint planning |  |\n  5119→| **P0** | **Add monotonic status guard.** Reject `done` -> any-earlier-status transitions when proof docs exist. | Next sprint planning |  |\n  5120→| **P1** | **Add circuit breaker.** If last 3 sessions performed identical actions, halt and alert. | Next sprint planning |  |\n  5121→| **P1** | **Re-read state from disk before every write.** Ralph must not rely on stale in-memory state. | Next sprint planning |  |\n  5122→| **P1** | **Attribute waste precisely.** Diff cost reports between session 16 and session 46 to get exact waste figure. Current estimate: ~$150. | Post-mortem |  |\n  5123→| **P2** | **Skip retros on no-op sessions.** If no stories were attempted, emit a 1-line \"no-op, skipping\" instead of a full retro. | Process improvement |  |\n  5124→\n  5125→---\n  5126→\n  5127→**Session 46 is the 16th consecutive no-op session and the 30th state corruption fix. The sprint has been done for 30+ sessions. Approximately $150 has been wasted on identical fixes. KILL RALPH.**\n  5128→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QHCNU17nFXSuMdixzgkNwM","session_id":"5a344c8a-9a77-441e-b5dd-8ef1